radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation without focal lesions. Normal pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands. Normal-sized kidneys, no focal renal lesions or hydronephrosis. The appendix is dilated to 9-10mm with a thickened, hyperemic wall. Mild haziness/stranding of the periappendiceal fat. Small amount of free fluid in the pelvis. A 1.6 cm corpus luteal cyst in the right adnexa.
